---
import "@fontsource/fragment-mono";
import "../styles/global.scss";
import "../styles/sidebar.scss";
import { ViewTransitions } from 'astro:transitions';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" href="https://em-content.zobj.net/thumbs/240/apple/354/globe-showing-asia-australia_1f30f.png">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <meta name="description" content="Links to corners of the web" />
    <title>Links</title>
    <ViewTransitions />
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="sidebar-container">
      <span class="name">
        <a class="name-link" href="/">Uyen Dien</a>
      </span>
      <div style={{ maxWidth: "350px" }}>
        I reside in many corners of the web. I collect things on ✶✶ <a
          class="wavy-link"
          href="https://www.are.na/uyen-dien"
          target="_blank">Are.na</a
        >. I always have my hands full with side projects, which I publish on
        💻 <a
          class="wavy-link"
          href="https://github.com/uyennie"
          target="_blank">GitHub</a
        > wherever possible. 
        Most of these projects are what I call my 'silly sites', where I practice my fundamental HTML and CSS skills. For the no-funny-business side of things, see my 💼 <a
          class="wavy-link"
          href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/uyendien"
          target="_blank">LinkedIn</a
        >. I have an 📸 <a
          class="wavy-link"
          href="https://www.instagram.com/onoffmilk/"
          target="_blank">Instagram</a
        > dedicated to illustrations that I'm slowly growing and curating. 
        I've always been a big movie person but I've been
        watching a lot more of them over the past year, and was persuaded to make
        a 🍿 <a
          class="wavy-link"
          href="https://letterboxd.com/uyend"
          target="_blank">Letterboxd</a
        >, so I have that too. Though, most times, I'm procrastinating by curating the perfect listening experience for any mood that may occur on 🎧 <a
          class="wavy-link"
          href="https://open.spotify.com/user/uyen_dien?si=67847a028f954f30"
          target="_blank">Spotify</a
        >. Phew.
      </div>
      <div style={{ paddingBottom: "55px" }}>
        <a href="/">← Home</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
